Japanese Bought Net 1470.2 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week

-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 
2011-09-29T00:02:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/japanese-bought-net-1470-2-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Sept. 23 according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors released by
the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 1470.2 billion yen ($19.2 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, bought 32.8 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 12.4 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 1490.6 billion yen.  Foreign investors sold 655 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 58.4 billion yen in stocks, and sold 578.7 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 1292.1
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Minh Bui in Tokyo at   mbui@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  